The paper deals with information theory and its application to machine learning, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses principles of decision-making, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of probability mass functions and random variables suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the interpretation of the measure in terms of decisions an agent should take, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
